# run artifacts -- reproducible from code, not version-controlled
__pycache__/
*.pyc
gate_*.json
logs/*.out
logs/*.err
results/*.csv
# NOTE: the per-run records results/*.json (one per method x structure x D x seed) ARE
# version-controlled (~3.5 MB, plain git): they are the provenance from which aggregate.py
# rebuilds the corrected T1-T5 tables, so a repo-only reviewer can regenerate every LIM-ENSO
# aggregate without the cluster. (gate_*.json scratch stays ignored above; agg/*.csv are tracked.)
# NOTE: llm_cache/*.json (the accepted LLM-emitted Scheme per structure) IS version-controlled:
# it is the program-as-data experimental artifact, so reruns load the exact generated programs
# (one MindRouter hit per structure) rather than re-querying a non-deterministic API.
